This paper is likely to belong to the Computer Science sub-category of Network and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) as it discusses the use of Information-Centric Networking (ICN) to enhance CoAP services for IoT devices. It may also belong to the sub-category of Cryptography and Security (cs.CR) as it discusses the security implications of using ICN for CoAP observe. Additionally, it may be relevant to the sub-categories of Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) and Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) as it discusses the benefits of ICN for reducing communication overhead and state management. Finally, it may be relevant to the sub-category of Systems and Control (cs.SY) as it discusses the potential benefits of ICN for network providers and CoAP applications.
